# Design system — page shell (AppShell)

Routes rendered inside `AppShell` already sit in a wrapper with `p-5` (`AppShell.tsx`). Do **not** add extra page gutters on the route root or the header will sit lower than the showcase.

## Correct page root (inside AppShell)

```tsx
<div className={uiCx('w-full min-w-0', uiSpacing.pageStack, 'min-h-full bg-gray-50')}>
  <AppPageHeader ... />  {/* first child — no margin-top, no pt/py on wrapper */}
  ...
</div>
```

Reference: `DesignSystemShowcase.tsx`, `Customers.tsx`, `BusinessDashboard.tsx`.

## Forbidden on AppShell routes

- `uiSpacing.pageY` or `uiSpacing.pageX` on the page root (`py-4`, `px-4 md:px-6`, `pt-*`, extra `p-5`/`p-6`)
- Duplicate outer padding “because the migration checklist says pageY”
- `mt-*` / `pt-*` on `AppPageHeader` or a wrapper above it

`pageY` / `pageX` are only for layouts **without** AppShell padding (standalone pages, portaled full-bleed UIs).

## Before finishing a visual migration

1. Page root uses `pageStack` + `bg-gray-50` only (optional `main`/`div`, no vertical gutter tokens).
2. `AppPageHeader` is the first child.
3. Compare top spacing to `/dev/design-system` in the running app — header top edge should align with showcase, not sit ~16–24px lower.
